snippet.textDisplay: Ok so if any of y’all are hammer experts in the comments, I have a question:                                        Why use a narrower offset dovetail that needs a key when you could just use a normal dovetail and a removable pin (like some big 1/2“ round) that goes through the joint and keeps the die from sliding? This way you just remove the pin and slide the dovetail right out. I don’t see why the key method is better than that. I’m just 16 so sorry if I screwed up some terminology.
